<TITLE> Stanchart CEO faces arrest </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 22 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court has ordered arrest of Standard Chartered Bank CEO after a client sued him for allegedly taking away her car by force. Dhaka's chief metropolitan judge ordered on Monday that Osman Morad and the bank's collection manager for the city's Dhanmondi branch be arrested, a TV station reported. ATN Bangla, quoting court documents, said Afroza Jamil, the client, borrowed Tk 16,65,000 to buy a microbus and was to repay in 60 monthly instalments. She paid back Tk 7 lakh in 19 months and then missed three consecutive payments. She alleged the bank had not given any notice before taking away the microbus using "the hired goons" of a debt collection agency called Credit Care. The case was filed back in March this year, and police conducted a five-month inquiry. The court order was based on the police report, the TV station said. The officer in charge at Dhamondi Police Station, Syed Mohsinul Huq, confirmed the warrant of arrest against collection manager Zia Hasan Chowdhury. "I've received one warrant," he told bdnews24.com. bdn
